
[1]risk

   RISK, n.

   1. Hazard; danger; peril; exposure to harm. He, at the risk of his
   life, saved a drowning man.

   2. In commerce, the hazard of loss, either of ship, goods or other
   property. Hence, risk signifies also the degree of hazard or danger;
   for the premiums of insurance are calculated upon the risk. The
   underwriters now take risks at a low premium.

   To run a risk, is to incur hazard; to encounter danger.

                                 RISK, v.t.

   1. To hazard; to endanger; to expose to injury or loss; as, to risk
   goods on board of a ship; to risk one's person in battle; to risk one's
   fame by a publication; to risk life in defense of rights.

   2. To venture; to dare to undertake; as, to risk a battle or combat.
